Pumpkin Pie
Judy Heumann

Crust:

Mix:

1 1/2 - 1 3/4 cups flour
1 tsp salt

Measure 1/3 cup of this mixture into a small bowl.  Add:

1/4 cup water

and stir to make a smooth paste.  Using a pastry blende, cut:

2/3 cups crisco

into the flour/salt mixture until it is the size of small peas.  Stir the flour paste into the dough.  Work it with your hand until it is well incorporated and the dough may be gathered into a ball.  Roll into a large circle to make the pie shell.

Pie filling:

1 can (15-16oz) pumpkin
1 can (12oz) evaporated milk
1/4 cup brown sugar
1/2 cup white sugar
1/2 tsp salt
1 tsp cinnamon
1/2 tsp ginger
1/4 allspice or nutmeg
1/8 tsp cloves
2 eggs, slightly beaten

Mix together and pour into pie shell.  Bake 15 minutes at 425F, then reduce heat to 350F for about 45 minutes. or when a knife inserted into the pie comes out clean.  Serve with sweetened whip cream.
